  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Chankan: The Forever Man was an Action Platformer for the Sega Megadrive/Genesis.\nThe game featured an uncommonly dark premise for the time of its release, which saw the home console market flooded with licensed platformers based on family-friendly media.\n\nIt is based upon a comic book by Robert A. Kraus and was produced by Ed Annunziata, who met Chakan's creator at a convention and was impressed.",
